text: Rozina Cambos (; December 17, 1951 – December 4, 2012) was a Romanian-born Israeli actress.Rozina Cambos’s filmography (in Hebrew) After emigrating to Israel from Romania in 1983, she became popular as a stage actress at the Habima Theatre and the Cameri Theatre. She also starred in several movies such as the 2010 film The Human Resources Manager. ==Death== Cambos died of leukaemia on December 4, 2012, aged 60. ==Other websites== * ==References== Category:1951 births Category:2012 deaths Category:Romanian Jews Category:Israeli stage actors Category:Israeli movie actors Category:Jewish Israeli actors Category:Deaths from leukemia Category:Israeli television actors Category:Cancer deaths in Israel Category:Naturalized citizens of Israel
